    {
      "text": "Pinobee: Wings of Adventure, known in Japan as Pinobee no Daibōken (ピノビィーの大冒険, Pinobī no Daibōken; lit. \"Pinobee's Great Adventure\") or Pinobee: Quest of Heart, is a 2D platformer for the Game Boy Advance, developed by Artoon and published by Hudson Soft. The game was released as a launch title for the system, on March 21, 2001 in Japan and June 11, 2001 in North America. A version was developed for PlayStation in 2002, simply titled Pinobee outside Japan.\nA sequel, Pinobee & Phoebee, was released only in Japan in 2002.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
